      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "QIIME 2 plugin to find acquired antimicrobial resistance genes and point mutations in protein and/or assembled nucleotide sequences with AMRFinderPlus."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "depth": 2,
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "Installation"
          }
        ],
        "identifier": "installation",
        "label": "Installation",
        "html_id": "installation",
        "implicit": true
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "To install "
          },
          {
            "type": "emphasis",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "value": "q2-amrfinderplus"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": ", follow the steps described in the\n"
          },
          {
            "type": "link",
            "url": "https://library.qiime2.org/quickstart/pathogenome",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "value": "QIIME 2 installation instructions"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "\nfor the pathogenome distribution. The pathogenome distribution is only available for\nlinux. If you want to install q2-amrfinderplus on macOS you can install it with the\ntiny distribution. For this follow the instructions on the "
          },
          {
            "type": "link",
            "url": "https://library.qiime2.org/plugins/bokulich-lab/q2-amrfinderplus",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "value": "QIIME2 Library"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "depth": 2,
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "Functionality"
          }
        ],
        "identifier": "functionality",
        "label": "Functionality",
        "html_id": "functionality",
        "implicit": true
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": "This QIIME 2 plugin contains actions used to annotate protein sequences MAGs and\ncontigs with antimicrobial resistance genes. The underlying tool used is\n"
          },
          {
            "type": "link",
            "url": "https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pathogens/antimicrobial-resistance/AMRFinder/",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "value": "AMRFinderPlus"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "value": ".\nFor a tutorial on the package, please refer to the "
          },
          {
            "type": "link",
            "url": "https://moshpit.qiime2.org/en/stable/chapters/tutorials/amr-gene-annotation/q2-amrfinderplus/intro/",
            "children": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "value": "MOSHPIT docs"
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
